## 🔒 PRIVACY & SECURITY RULES

- **Never** log audio or transcripts to third-party analytics.
- All AI API calls go through Next.js API routes — API keys never exposed to client.
- Audio processing happens locally via Web Audio API before sending to Deepgram.
- Session data stored encrypted in Supabase with row-level security.
- Screen capture exclusion is a non-negotiable product requirement — test
  on every OS/browser combination before shipping.

---

## 🚀 PERFORMANCE RULES

- **Lighthouse target**: Performance ≥ 90, Accessibility ≥ 95, Best Practices ≥ 95.
- Lazy-load all below-fold sections with `React.lazy + Suspense`.
- Three.js scene loaded only on hero section mount, destroyed on unmount.
- Images: Next.js `<Image>` with `priority` only on LCP element.
- Fonts: `font-display: swap`, subset to Latin, preload critical weights.
- Bundle: No component over 50KB gzipped. Code-split at route level.
- Web Vitals targets: LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1.

